Explain modes — seeing inside Catalyst.

The explain method has five modes you can pass.

Simple, the default, shows just the physical plan.

Extended shows all four plans — parsed, analyzed, optimized, and physical.

Codegen shows the generated java virtual machine code per stage.

Cost shows the optimized plan with row-count estimates per node.

Formatted shows the physical plan plus a separate operator-details section.

Same query, multiple lenses. The notebook runs a small group-by aggregation against the five-customer dataframe through three of the modes — simple, extended, and formatted — so you can compare what each one shows.
